<br>
What it boils down to, is that in a server that could have anywhere from hundreds to several thousand users connected to it, offloading the Disk stuff to the SCSI controller makes sense.  And you pay for it.  In a machine you use at your desk, your processor is so fast that it is actually faster to use IDE, and you get more for your buck.  There is more overhead in the SCSI command set then in the command set used by IDE type drives.  If you had a high enough workload, because SCSI will reorder requests and so on you end up getting better performance.  As a single user you're more likely to be impacted by the extra overhead of SCSI then you are to see any performance gains. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.showMessage?topicID=159.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.showMessage?topicID=157.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.emailToFriend?topicID=154.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.threadControl?topicID=154.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=154.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=154.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td 